collections.name: RingCentral API
collections.description:
This is a beta interactive API explorer for the RingCentral Connect Platform. To use this service, you will need to have an account with the proper credentials to generate an OAuth2 access token.

Quick Start

  1. 1) Go to Authentication > /oauth/token
  2. 2) Enter app_key, app_secret, username, password fields and then click "Try it out!"
  3. 3) Upon success, your access_token is loaded and you can access any form requiring authorization.

Links

  • RingCentral SDKs on Github
  • RingCentral Developer Support Email
https://developer.ringcentral.com

collections.name: RingCentral API - 2016-11-16
collections.description:
This is a collection of API requests associated with the Basic usage plan in RingCentral Connect Platform.

Please create a new Environment in Postman:

1. appKey: App key for your application
2. appSecret: App Secret for your application
3. rcUsername: RingCentral username (must be same environment as the API keys used above)
4. rcPassword: RingCentral password (must be same environment as the API keys used above)
5. rcExtension: RingCentral extension
6. rcApiBaseUri: https://platform[.devtest].ringcentral.com/restapi

This Postman Collection is configured for use with applications which have been configured to have Application Types which support "Password Flow" OAuth2 authentication workflows.

You must call the Auth endpoint first (this will then cache the access_token for use with all other API resources made available in this Postman collection).

requests.name: Get Token
requests.description:
Obtain a RingCentral access_token using Password Flow.

This should only be used when RingCentral API Keys are associated with an app which supports "Password Flow" OAuth2 as indicated in the RingCentral Developer Portal on the "Settings" page for the app respectively.

Default TTL for access_token is 60 minutes.

Propertyto
Data typeContact Info object
DescriptionRecipient information. phoneNumber property is mandatory
Propertyresolution
Data type
DescriptionFax resolution
PropertysendTime
Data typedatetime
DescriptionOptional. Timestamp to send fax at. If not specified (current or the past),the faxissent immediately
PropertycoverIndex
Data typeInteger (0-13)
DescriptionOptional. Cover page index. If not specified, the default coverpagewhichisconfigured in "Outbound FaxSettings" is attached. See also "Available Cover Pages" tablebelow
PropertycoverPageText
Data typestring
DescriptionOptional. Cover page text, entered by the fax sender and printed on thecoverpage.Maximum length is limited to 1024 symbols
